  ### Optional and mandatory fields

  - only ask for the information you absolutely need
  - if you do ask for optional information, mark the labels of optional fields with '(optional)'
  - don't mark mandatory fields with asterisks

  ### Labels

  - all form fields should be given labels
  - don't hide labels, unless the surrounding context makes them unnecessary
  - labels should be aligned above their fields
  - label text should be short, direct and in sentence case
  - avoid colons at the end of labels
  - labels should be associated with form fields using the `for` attribute

= model
  .form-group
    label.form-label for="full-name-1" Full name
    input#full-name-1.form-control type="text"

markdown:
  ### Form fields

  Make field widths proportional to the input they take.

  Ensure that users can enter the information they need at smaller screen sizes.

  Snap form fields to 100% width at smaller screen sizes.

  ### Fieldsets and legends

  Use fieldsets to group related form controls. The first element inside a fieldset must be a `legend` element which describes the group.

  ### Form focus states

  All elements use the yellow focus style as a highlight, as either a fill or 3px outline.

  Click on the label "Full name" or inside the form field to show the focus state.

= model
  .form-group
    label.form-label for="full-name-2" Full name
    input#full-name-2.form-control type="text"


h3 Spacing between form elements
p Ensure there is sufficient spacing between form elements.

= model
  .form-group
    label.form-label for="first-name" First name
    input#first-name.form-control type="text"

  .form-group
    label.form-label for="last-name" Last name
    input#last-name.form-control type="text"


markdown:
  ### Hint text

  - don't use placeholder text in form fields, as this will disappear once content is entered into the form field
  - use hint text for supporting contextual help, this will always be shown
  - hint text should sit above a form field
  - ensure hint text can be read correctly by screen readers

= model
  .form-group
    label.form-label for="ni-number" National Insurance number
    .form-hint It'll be on your last payslip. For example, JH 21 90 0A.
    input#ni-number-2.form-control type="text"

markdown:
  ### Radio buttons

  - use these to let users choose a single option from a list
  - for more than two options, radio buttons should be stacked
  - radio buttons with large hit areas are easier to select with a mouse or touch devices

= model 'radio-inline'
  .form-group.inline
    label.block-label for="radio-inline-1"
      input#radio-inline-1 type="radio" name="radio-inline-group" value="Yes" Yes
    label.block-label for="radio-inline-2"
      input#radio-inline-2 type="radio" name="radio-inline-group" value="No" No

= model 'radio'
  label.block-label.selected for="radio-1"
    input#radio-1 type="radio" name="radio-group" value="ni" Northern Ireland
  label.block-label for="radio-2"
    input#radio-2 type="radio" name="radio-group" value="isle-of-man-channel" Isle of Man or the Channel Islands
  p.form-block or
  label.block-label for="radio-3"
    input#radio-3 type="radio" name="radio-group" value="british-abroad" I am a British citizen living abroad

markdown:
  ### Checkboxes

  - use these to select either on/off toggles or multiple selections
  - make it clear with words when users can select one or multiple options

= model 'checkboxes'
  fieldset
    legend.form-label-bold Which types of waste do you transport regularly?
    p Select all that apply
    label.block-label.selected for="checkbox-1"
      input#checkbox-1 type="checkbox" value="animals" Waste from animal carcasses
    label.block-label for="checkbox-2"
      input#checkbox-2 type="checkbox" value="mines" Waste from mines or quarries
    label.block-label for="checkbox-3"
      input#checkbox-3 type="checkbox" value="agriculture" Farm or agricultural waste

p Large hit areas aren't always appropriate.

= model 'inline-checkbox'
  .form-group
    label.form-label for="phone-number" Enter your telephone number
    input#phone-number.form-control type="text"
    label.form-checkbox for="phone-number-checkbox"
      input#phone-number-checkbox type="checkbox" value="1" I need to be contacted using a text phone

h3 Inset form elements
p Insets can be used within forms to emphasise supporting information.
p Click on "Yes" to see how this works.

= model 'inset-radios'
  fieldset
    legend Do you know their National Insurance number?
    .form-group.inline
      label.block-label for="radio-inline-11"
        input#radio-inline-11 type="radio" name="radio-inline-group" value="Yes" Yes
      label.block-label for="radio-inline-12"
        input#radio-inline-12 type="radio" name="radio-inline-group" value="No" No
    .panel-indent data-controlled-by="radio-inline-group" data-control-value="Yes"
      label.form-label for="ni-number-2" National Insurance number
      input#ni-number-2.form-control type="text"

p Click on "Citizen of a different country" to see how this works.

= model 'inset-checkboxes'
  fieldset
    legend.form-label-bold What is your nationality?
    p Select all options that are relevant to you.
    .form-group
      label.block-label.selected for="inset-checkbox-1"
        input#inset-checkbox-1 type="checkbox" value="british" name="inset-checkbox"
          | British (including English, Scottish, Welsh and Northern Irish)
      label.block-label for="inset-checkbox-2"
        input#inset-checkbox-2 type="checkbox" value="irish" name="inset-checkbox"
          | Irish
      label.block-label for="inset-checkbox-3"
        input#inset-checkbox-3 type="checkbox" value="different" name="inset-checkbox"
          | Citizen of a different country

    .panel-indent data-controlled-by="inset-checkbox" data-control-value="different"
      label.form-label for="ni-country-name-1" Country name
      input#ni-number-2.form-control type="text" name="country-name"

